in the gymnasium today.

250
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,800
We worked out
a different system.

251
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:53,700
You think you can walk into
my institution, start changing
rules and causing riots?

252
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:56,700
- There was no riot.
- The prisoners refused orders,

253
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,800
and my guards had to use
force because of you.

254
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,700
The force wasn't necessary.
All the violence came from Mr Dacks.

255
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,100
He was trying
to provoke Powell.

256
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:08,700
Powell is dangerous, and he was
dealt with as a dangerous psychotic.

257
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:13,100
No, no, no.
He offered no danger, none.

258
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:16,900
Dr Murray, did Powell
behave in a threatening way...

259
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:20,600
at any time?

260
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:28,000
No.

261
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:35,000
- I'll have a talk with Mr Dacks.
- Splendid.

262
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,700
Meanwhile, your little game
compromised my authority...

263
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,900
and the authority
of my guards.

264
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:44,600
Do you know what that means
at a maximum security prison?

265
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:47,100
You put everyone at risk.

266
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:50,500
The safety of every man here rests with
me, Caulder, and I can't trust you.

267
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:54,000
And I want you out.

268
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:57,300
You have ten days.
And I'm being generous.

269
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:03,600
I have 15 days left in my evaluation.
I'll leave when I'm finished.

270
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:07,800
Now you have seven days.

271
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:38,200
- How does he have the...
- Hang on a second.

272
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:41,400
How does he have the right
to cut my evaluation time?

273
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,900
He doesn't,

274
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,900
but he has the power
to kick you out...

275
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,700
whenever he wants to
and bring in somebody else.

276
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,800
So write your conclusion.
Wrap it up.

277
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:57,700
If I have more time, I think I can
get him out of there.

278
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:03,100
What are you
talking about?

279
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:06,200
The hearing. I think
when the judge hears the man...

280
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:10,100
who he is, what he has to say...
I think he'll walk out of there.

281
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:13,300
You're not his defence attorney.

282
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:16,800
You're not his pal.
What are you after?

283
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,900
- Big time ending for the book?
- Not about a book.

284
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:24,300
- It's not about my career...
- It should be.

285
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:29,300
Theo, you walked
into this case...

286
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,300
under my guarantee,

287
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:35,600
with an opportunity
to further yourself.

288
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:38,700
Now, are you willing to put
all that at risk possibly,

289
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,700
damage your career
possibly,

290
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:43,800
embarrass me?

291
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:47,700
Sorry, yes.

292
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:54,100
Then stop complaining about the time
you have left and use it.

293
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:58,000
Push the man.
Shake him.

294
00:22:58,300 --> 00:23:00,800
- Where does the violence come from?
- I'm not sure...

295
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,800
- The gorillas?
- I'm not sure of the connection.

296
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,000
Well, find it.

297
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:07,800
The only way he is ever going
to get out of that place...

298
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:12,300
is for you to make that judge
feel that Powell is sane and safe.

299
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:14,700
You show where
the violence came from,

300
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:18,300
and you show
that the violence has gone.

301
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,300
- Can you do that?
- Yes.

302
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:26,400
Good.
You're on your own.

303
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:33,700
Thanks.

304
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,700
- See you later.
- I'll call you later.

305
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:40,300
Okay.

306
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:45,600
Hello.
This is a surprise.

307
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:47,600
Sorry. I, uh...

308
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:52,500
- The message said you'd be home
after 7:00, so...
- So you came by to check?

309
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:55,300
Were you hall monitor
in school?

310
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,800
Yes, I was.

311
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:05,300
Funny, I never got a sense
of you in your parents' house.

312
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:08,900
- This is definitely more...
- Messy?

313
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:11,900
More you.

314
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:14,600
So...

315
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:17,300
what did he do to you
this time?

316
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,300
I don't see
any cuts or bruises.

317
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:24,000
This time
it wasn't him.

318
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:30,500
I only have seven days left
with your father. That's it.

319
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,800
Are they going to take
the case away from you?

320
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,400
Case.

321
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:44,200
It's not a...

322
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:47,300
not a case any more.

323
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:51,100
It's not a book either.

324
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:55,600
He may break my neck tomorrow, but I
think I'm becoming a friend of his...

325
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:57,700
and his student.

326
00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:01,200
His "Tabibu Juha".

327
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:06,100
He calls you that?

328
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:08,800
I think "Tabibu"
means "doctor".

329
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,900
Yes, it does.

330
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:18,200
What does "Juha" mean?

331
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:21,800
"Juha" means...

332
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:25,200
"idiot".

333
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:33,900
Yeah.

334
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:39,900
Well, I must be, because
I can't figure this one out.

335
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:45,100
He knows I can't bring
a gorilla into his cell and...

336
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:48,700
What?

337
00:25:49,300 --> 00:25:51,700
What?

338
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:04,300
- Where are we going?
- Fresh air, a ride in the country.

339
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:08,900
You'll like it. It's wilderness
all the way. They're waiting for us.

340
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,700
Who? What are you
planning, "Juha"?

341
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:13,900
I'm not your idiot any more.

342
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:17,100
- You finally looked it up.
- No.

343
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:21,000
Your daughter told me.

344
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,500
Watch your step.

345
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:57,000
The gorillas are
in the cage room now.

346
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,300
- Whoa!

347
00:27:24,700 --> 00:27:28,900
Jesus Christ.

348
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:40,500
The old silverback's
been with us the longest.

349
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:43,500
You remember him, Dr Powell.
He's the one you...

350
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:47,900
I'm sorry. We need
to be alone in here.

351
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:54,600
The restraints?

352
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:59,400
I'll put them back on him
before we leave.

353
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:09,100
You understand if he comes out of
that door without them on...

354
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:30,000
I thought you'd feel
safer here.

355
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:35,400
I thought if you were around them,
you'd talk to me.

356
00:28:35,700 --> 00:28:39,600
Tell me about the violence,
about the killing.

357
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:42,600
These are shadows
of gorillas.

358
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:46,300
Born in cages.

359
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:51,300
Only the old male...
he was free once.

360
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:53,800
Still alive.

361
00:28:54,100 --> 00:28:57,300
Goliath.

362
00:28:57,500 --> 00:29:00,900
I named him that.
I brought him here.

363
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:04,200
This cage has broken him.

364
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:08,500
Broken his heart,
broken his mind.

365
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:12,400
Made him insane.

366
00:29:12,700 --> 00:29:16,000
I did that.

367
00:29:16,900 --> 00:29:19,300
I understand that, Ethan.
I do.

368
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:23,500
But I need to know
about the killing.

369
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:29,900
There's a female
just like that one.

370
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:33,700
Was there ever
any violence among them?

371
00:29:33,900 --> 00:29:37,600
Was there any violence
towards you?

372
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:42,400
There were warnings.

373
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:45,000
Warnings.

374
00:30:09,700 --> 00:30:14,000
She was a good mother
and a good teacher.

375
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:18,600
The baby was always protected,
always instructed.

376
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:21,700
Always groomed,
always...

377
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:23,600
touched,

378
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:25,500
safe.

379
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:28,700
She used to watch
over him,

380
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:31,900
the way the old silverback
used to watch over...

381
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:34,500
all of us,

382
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:38,500
even me.

383
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:41,700
It's an amazing...

384
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:46,000
feeling, Theo,
to be watched over.

385
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:00,300
I discovered
in that look of his...

386
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:03,000
more than watchfulness...

387
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:05,500
tolerance,

388
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,600
acceptance.

389
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:11,700
- In fact, he was...

390
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,300
Ethan?

391
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:24,000
Ethan, what is it?

392
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,400
- What is it?

393
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:30,700
What's wrong?

394
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,600
- Shh. Shh.

395
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:37,400
- Shh.

396
00:36:19,100 --> 00:36:22,900
It was me.

397
00:36:22,900 --> 00:36:26,300
They'd found my things.

398
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:32,700
Been tracking me.

399
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:37,200
So I brought them.

400
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:40,700
I brought the... takers...

401
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,500
and death.

402
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,500
Still he looks at me
without blame.

403
00:36:48,700 --> 00:36:51,200
Because you're
not to blame,

404
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:54,100
not for any of it.

405
00:36:54,300 --> 00:36:58,000
You were just defending
your family.

406
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:21,500
- Ethan, close it.
- He won't come out.

407
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:26,900
You see?
Even if he can.

408
00:37:29,500 --> 00:37:33,000
Not far from here is a fence, and on
the other side of that fence is freedom,

409
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:35,800
and he can smell it.

410
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:39,000
He'll never try
to get there,

411
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:42,900
'cause he's given up.

412
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:48,900
By now he thinks freedom
is something he dreamed.

413
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:51,800
And you?

414
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:55,400
Have you given up?

415
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:58,600
Because we have a chance to get you
out of here now, a good chance.

416
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:03,100
This is all I need...
what you've told me.

417
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,800
It's not just something
you dreamed.

418
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:12,500
It's real.

419
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:44,600
- I'd like you to wear this
to the hearing today.
- Where'd you get that?

420
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:46,700
Lyn brought it.

421
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:51,000
She's still here.

422
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:03,500
- Ethan, you can do this.
- Leave it alone.

423
00:39:03,700 --> 00:39:06,100
What are you so afraid of?

424
00:39:06,300 --> 00:39:09,400
I don't want to hurt her.

425
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:12,600
You've already done that.

426
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:17,300
Remember the first thing you said
to me? The first word? Remember?

427
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:21,200
You told me to tell
your daughter goodbye.

428
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:24,800
Tell her yourself.

429
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:53,300
I don't know what to say.

430
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:57,200
How are you?

431
00:39:57,500 --> 00:40:01,400
That sounds stupid,
I guess.

432
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:06,500
I miss you.

433
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:11,300
Your father is a fool.

434
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,300
If you were just born, I would
pick you up and hold you...

435
00:40:14,500 --> 00:40:20,000
and take you everywhere with me
and never walk away from you.

436
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,600
You're such
a treasure, Lyn.

437
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:27,600
You're so much better
than your father. You don't hate.

438
00:40:27,900 --> 00:40:31,900
You don't even hate me.

439
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:36,200
You know that
when I went away from you,

440
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:41,300
I always took you
with me, inside.

441
00:40:42,900 --> 00:40:46,100
I would love
to believe that.

442
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:49,400
Well, this is all
I have left for you.

443
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:53,600
It's the only possession
I kept.

444
00:41:40,500 --> 00:41:42,700
You'll wait in your cell
till I come and get you.

445
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:46,900
The van'll be here in 25 minutes.
The hearing starts at 4:00. Understand?

446
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:49,600
You'll change out of
that pretty blue suit...

447
00:41:49,900 --> 00:41:51,800
and turn it over
for storage.

448
00:41:52,100 --> 00:41:53,900
- Any questions?
- Sorry, Ethan.

449
00:41:56,700 --> 00:42:01,200
Ethan, there was
nothing we could do.

450
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:13,100
Inside.

451
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:19,700
I said, "Inside"!

452
00:42:20,300 --> 00:42:22,500
Stop hitting him!
Stop hitting him!

453
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:25,300
- You think that's funny, Nicko?
- Just stop hitting him!

454
00:42:25,500 --> 00:42:29,200
Ow!

455
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:31,300
- I got Dacks!
- Oh, you wanna play, Pete?

456
00:42:31,500 --> 00:42:33,700
- No, no! Sorry, Mr Dacks.
- You think that's funny, Pete?

457
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,400
- Huh? You think that's funny?
- It was an accident.

458
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:39,500
- You want to play? Come here.
- No, you can't come in here.

459
00:42:39,700 --> 00:42:41,700
You can't come in, Mr Dacks.
You can't come in.

460
00:42:41,900 --> 00:42:45,300
No, Mr Dacks.
No, don't be bad, Mr Dacks.

461
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,700
You wanna play "Can't Come In"?
We'll play.

462
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:50,200
- No! Mr Dacks!
- Let's play, Pete.

463
00:42:50,500 --> 00:42:52,200
- No!
- You wanna play, Pete?

464
00:42:52,500 --> 00:42:54,100
- No!
- Well, let's play!

465
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:57,400
- Ow! No! Ow!

466
00:42:57,700 --> 00:43:00,700
You want to play?
Think this is for fun?

467
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,900
Huh?

468
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,300
- Aah!

469
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:25,200
Damn it! Lock this place down!

470
00:43:25,500 --> 00:43:27,500
- I want this place locked down!

471
00:43:27,700 --> 00:43:29,800
Anderson, secure the block
and cuff that son of a bitch!

472
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:32,200
Get back in there!
Settle down!

473
00:43:32,400 --> 00:43:36,900
- Shut up! Shut up!

474
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:45,100
I heard. You want
to stay for supper?

475
00:43:45,300 --> 00:43:49,700
- I blew it. I lost him.
He's silent again.

476
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:53,100
It's over.
Let it go.

477
00:43:53,300 --> 00:43:56,900
He was protecting
his family... again.

478
00:43:57,100 --> 00:43:59,300
I should have been with him
every minute.

479
00:43:59,500 --> 00:44:02,800
Let it go.

480
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:06,500
And don't worry...
about anything.

481
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:10,500
I'll speak to Josephson,
smooth things over.

482
00:44:10,700 --> 00:44:12,400
I'll help you cut
your losses.

483
00:44:12,700 --> 00:44:16,700
And his losses?

484
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,000
It's true, isn't it?

485
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:21,000
He'll never get out
of there.

486
00:44:21,300 --> 00:44:23,100
It was never your job
to get him out of there.

487
00:44:23,300 --> 00:44:26,400
Theo, there is nothing
to be done.

488
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:28,300
Know when to walk away.

489
00:44:28,500 --> 00:44:31,800
You help the ones you can.

490
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:37,400
I'm sorry. I've let you down,
and I barged in here...

491
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:40,900
Theo.

492
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:48,100
If you don't let this end,
you'll do yourself damage.

493
00:44:48,300 --> 00:44:51,900
You got involved...
emotionally. It happens.

494
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:56,100
Now you have to get
your focus back.

495
00:44:56,400 --> 00:44:59,700
You're losing control.

496
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:04,400
Wouldn't that be nice?

497
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:14,200
Mealtime!
Line 'em up!

498
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:18,500
- You heard him. Let's go.
- Single file!

499
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:28,500
I'm ready,
I'm ready, I'm ready.

500
00:45:28,700 --> 00:45:30,400
Dr Caulder,
what's wrong with him?

501
00:45:30,600 --> 00:45:33,100
- Nicko, back in line.
- Dr Caulder...

502
00:45:33,300 --> 00:45:35,300
Any change?

503
00:45:35,600 --> 00:45:37,300
Not a word in three days.

504
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:39,800
- Sorry.
- Hey, ape man!

505
00:45:40,100 --> 00:45:41,700
He said mealtime!

506
00:45:41,900 --> 00:45:45,800
Can you leave him there,
Dacks?

507
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:57,300
Keep your hands
at your side!

508
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:29,000
I'm sorry, Ethan.

509
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:35,400
I don't know if you can hear me,
but this is my last day, so...

510
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:42,000
I put Dacks up on charges.

511
00:46:42,300 --> 00:46:46,000
I still might be able to get you
that hearing, if you would just speak.

512
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:50,500
If you would just come back.

513
00:46:52,300 --> 00:46:55,900
Okay, Ethan.

514
00:47:04,700 --> 00:47:06,300
You asked me
a question once.

515
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:08,700
"What has you
all tied up in knots...

516
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:11,400
when you wake up sweating
in the middle of the night?"

517
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:14,000
You still wanna know?

518
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:17,500
I've been thinking about it.
I've been thinking about it a lot.

519
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:20,800
It's not the work.
I love the work.

520
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:24,400
I've always loved the work.

521
00:47:24,700 --> 00:47:27,900
It's the game.

522
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,900
The game, Ethan.

523
00:47:30,100 --> 00:47:33,000
And I was so good at it.

524
00:47:33,300 --> 00:47:37,100
I made sure all
the right people liked me.

525
00:47:37,300 --> 00:47:39,600
At night, I'd do
the checklist in my mind.

526
00:47:39,900 --> 00:47:41,500
Am I cool with Ben Hillard?

527
00:47:41,800 --> 00:47:43,500
Am I cool with Dr Josephson?

528
00:47:43,700 --> 00:47:45,800
Am I cool with all the people
who can help me?

529
00:47:46,100 --> 00:47:50,100
Am I cool with all the people
who can hurt me?

530
00:47:50,300 --> 00:47:53,500
Nobody thought I was weak
or a loser.

531
00:47:53,800 --> 00:47:57,900
There was nobody
I was offending,

532
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:01,500
nobody I loved.

533
00:48:05,200 --> 00:48:08,900
"That" game, Ethan.

534
00:48:09,900 --> 00:48:13,700
But guess what?

535
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:16,400
You taught me how
to live outside of the game.

536
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:28,300
You taught me how to live.

537
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:34,900
And you know what
scares me even more?

538
00:48:35,100 --> 00:48:37,200
That I'm going back in.

539
00:48:37,400 --> 00:48:40,100
"Forgive me, Ben.
Put me back in the game."

540
00:48:40,300 --> 00:48:43,000
"I'll make you like me again!
I'll do the work."

541
00:48:43,300 --> 00:48:47,200
"I'll do all the work,
just put me back in the game!"

542
00:48:47,500 --> 00:48:50,100
And do you wanna know...

543
00:48:50,400 --> 00:48:53,100
You wanna know the psychology
behind this?

544
00:48:53,300 --> 00:48:57,500
Now, pay attention,
because I'm good at this.

545
00:48:57,800 --> 00:49:02,200
I'm trying not to say
goodbye to you.

546
00:49:06,200 --> 00:49:11,400
I'm trying not to say
I'll miss you.

547
00:49:16,600 --> 00:49:21,300
I'm trying to forget you.

548
00:49:25,400 --> 00:49:30,100
Ethan Powell, case closed.

549
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:34,100
Case closed!

550
00:49:35,100 --> 00:49:38,400
Look at me.

551
00:50:19,900 --> 00:50:25,500
- Come on!

552
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:32,600
Oh, come on!

553
00:50:32,900 --> 00:50:36,400
- Take the bat
off your shoulders, you bum!
- Calm down, Dacks!

554
00:50:36,700 --> 00:50:39,300
Hey, on a three-two count you gotta
protect the plate, you moron!

555
00:50:39,500 --> 00:50:42,300
- Three and one,
Dacks, not three and two.
- First base.

556
00:50:42,600 --> 00:50:44,700
- I would protect the plate.
- We're on first base.

557
00:50:44,900 --> 00:50:47,100
- You gotta protect the plate.
- Right, the plate.

558
00:50:47,300 --> 00:50:50,700
- Protect the plate.

559
00:50:51,000 --> 00:50:54,400
- You see? You see? You see?

560
00:50:54,600 --> 00:50:56,300
You take the lumber off
the shelf and you get a hit.

561
00:50:56,600 --> 00:50:59,000
- Peter! Hey, come on!

562
00:50:59,300 --> 00:51:01,800
- Pete, put it back in! Pete, please!

563
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:06,600
- Put it back in, Pete!
- Hey, Pete!

564
00:51:06,900 --> 00:51:12,100
Give me the plug, Pete!
Give me the plug!

565
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:16,900
- Give me the plug now!
- Stop! Stop it!

566
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:23,100
Peter, give Guard Anderson
the plug. It's his birthday.

567
00:51:23,300 --> 00:51:28,100
That's right, Pete.
It's my birthday.

568
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:30,900
You wanna give me
a present?

569
00:51:31,100 --> 00:51:33,600
Come on, buddy.
Let me have it.

570
00:51:33,900 --> 00:51:35,500
- That's it. Let go.
- All right, all right.

571
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:40,200
- Plug it in. Come on.
- There you go.

572
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:42,700
Are you gonna leave it alone now?

573
00:51:45,200 --> 00:51:49,700
- For you.
- Okay. For me.

574
00:52:20,100 --> 00:52:22,500
Hey, Dr Caulder's here!
Glad to see you, Doc.

575
00:52:22,800 --> 00:52:26,000
Hey! Caulder's back!
Welcome back, Doctor!

576
00:52:26,300 --> 00:52:29,100
Anything he does out there
is gonna come down on my head,

577
00:52:29,300 --> 00:52:31,800
and I'm gonna come down
on yours!

578
00:52:32,100 --> 00:52:34,500
Heard you were long gone
back to the city. I thought
you were all through here.

579
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:38,900
- I came back to talk to Powell.
- Well, your highflier's
gone out the window!

580
00:52:39,100 --> 00:52:40,800
Went through a hole
in the fence.

581
00:52:41,100 --> 00:52:43,700
We think he scaled the other one.
He must have had some help!

582
00:52:43,900 --> 00:52:49,900
And he even wrote
a little note... to you!

583
00:52:54,500 --> 00:52:59,600
Can you make heads or tails
of that? I sure can't.

584
00:53:03,900 --> 00:53:05,900
What?

585
00:53:06,100 --> 00:53:09,800
- You're never gonna find him.
- You know where he is?

586
00:53:13,700 --> 00:53:15,300
You're never
gonna find him.

587
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:18,800
- If you got any idea where...
- If you're holding out on me,
you could be aiding an escapee.

588
00:53:19,000 --> 00:53:24,200
That is a felony, and I could
have you arrested for that!

589
00:53:27,700 --> 00:53:30,200
I'm beginning
to like it here.

590
00:53:30,500 --> 00:53:32,100
"Dear Theo."

591
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:34,900
"I'm sorry I'm not there
to say goodbye."

592
00:53:35,100 --> 00:53:37,700
"You were right.
Freedom is not just a dream."

593
00:53:37,900 --> 00:53:42,600
"It's there on the other side of those
fences we build all by ourselves."

594
00:53:42,900 --> 00:53:47,300
"Thank you for giving me hope and for
giving me back my daughter."

595
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:51,700
"And I thank you, Theo, for sharing
this journey with me."

596
00:53:51,900 --> 00:53:55,400
"Your friend, Ethan."

